Adenanthos venosus is a flowering plant from the family Proteaceae that can be found in Western Australia where it Declared to be Rare Flora. It is 0.4–2 metres (1 ft 4 in–6 ft 7 in) long and have either red or pink coloured flowers. The flowers remain in such colour only for one month in winter and then become greyish-white from May to December.
